The paper discusses advances in deep learning methods for machine reading and open-domain question answering, which are topics that are commonly studied in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on training neural network rankers for open-domain QA, which is a task that involves both information retrieval and machine reading. Therefore, it is likely that the paper belongs to one or more of these sub-categories.
